  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nIn the Coorparoo testnet, prior to the Altair activation, Teku was able to find and connect to the two bootnodes fine (they were the only other nodes to find).\n\nBut after the Altair slot, any newly started Teku could not connect to the bootnodes via discovery anymore (but could if connecting to them as static peers).\n\nMost likely the eth2 field in the ENR was not updated with the new fork digest for Altair and so the nodes weren't considered suitable peers and ignored.",
